=== notes ===
- 7z 10 Gbps: peel essentially ties baseline (1.04×, ~10 ms slower
  on a 256 MiB archive). Pre-fix this cell was 4.39×; the closing
  came from streaming the packed bytes through SparseFileSliceReader,
  switching the per-substream and folder-wide CRC32 to slicing-by-16
  (zip::crc32::Crc32 instead of hash::crc32::Crc32), bumping the
  CopyCoder's read buffer from 8 KiB (io::copy default) to 256 KiB,
  and dropping the per-substream sync_all in SevenzSink::end_substream.
- 7z 1 Gbps: peel beats baseline (0.78× vs 1.26× pre-fix). The same
  streaming-overlap mechanism is what gets the win, since the wire
  is not yet fast enough to hide extraction time.
- All other cells: roughly unchanged from the pre-fix bench, modulo
  ~5 % run-to-run variance the README disclaims. The zip pipeline
  changes (cap respect + offset-order entry processing + EOCD/CD
  exemption) preserve the 0.24× headline at 10 Gbps × 256 MiB.
